<body>

<p>
	<h2>	
Ingredients:
	</h2>
</p>
<p>
1-Boneless chicken cubes 200g 
</p>

<p>
2-Soy sauce 1 tbs
</p>

<p>

3-Pink salt ¼ tsp or to taste
</p>

<p>

4-(Black pepper powder) ¼ tsp
</p>


<p>

5-Dried oregano ¼ tsp
</p>
 
<p>

6-Cooking oil 1 tbs 
</p>
<p>

7-Mushrooms sliced 1 Cup
</p>
<p>

8-Cooking oil 1 tsp 
</p>
<p>

9-Unsalted Butter2-3 tbs 
</p>

<p>

10-(Garlic) chopped 1 tbs
</p>

<p>

11-(All-purpose flour) 2 tbs
</p>

<p>

12-(Milk) 2 Cups or as required 
</p>

<p>

13-Cream 1/3 Cup
</p>

<p>

14-Cheddar cheese grated ½ Cup
</p>

<p>


15-(Red chili) crushed ½ tsp
</p>

<p>
16-Dried oregano ½ tsp
</p>

<p>
17-Pink salt ½ tsp or to taste 
</p>

<p>
18-(Black pepper) crushed ½ tsp 
</p>

<p>

19-Penne pasta 250g boiled as per pack’s instruction
</p>

<p>

20-Fresh parsley chopped 2 tbs 
</p>
<p>

21-(Red chili) crushed 
</p>
<p>

22-Fresh parsley chopped
 </p>


<p> 
<h3>
Directions: 
</h3>

</p>

<p>
1-In a bowl, add chicken, soy sauce, pink salt, black pepper powder, dried oregano & mix well.
</p>
<p>
2-In a wok, add cooking oil, seasoned chicken, mix well & cook on medium flame for 4-5 minutes.
</p>

<p>

3-Add mushrooms, mix well & cook for 1-2 minutes & set aside.
</p>

<p>

4-In same wok, add cooking oil,margarine & let it melt.
</p>

<p>

5-Add garlic & sauté for a minute.
</p>

<p>
6-Add all-purpose flour, mix well & cook on low flame for 1-2 minutes.
</p>

<p>

7-Gradually add milk, mix well & cook until it thickens. 
</p>

<p>

8-Turn off the flame, add cream, cheddar cheese, red crushed chili ,dried oregano, pink salt, black pepper crushed, mix well, turn on the flame & cook for 1-2 minutes.
</p>

<p>

9-Add pasta, cooked chicken & mushrooms, fresh parsley & give it a good mix.
</p>

10-Sprinkle red chili crushed, fresh parsley & serve!
</body>
